.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH memory 1  "memory " 
.SH NAME
memory \- Manage the agent\*(Aqs long\-term memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmemory\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Manage the agent\*(Aqs long\-term memory.
.PP
Memories persist across sessions and are included as context in every chat and task execution. Use them to teach the agent about your infrastructure, preferences, and patterns.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
memory\-list(1)
List all memories, optionally filtered by category
.TP
memory\-search(1)
Search memories by content
.TP
memory\-save(1)
Save a new memory
.TP
memory\-update(1)
Update an existing memory by ID
.TP
memory\-delete(1)
Delete a memory by ID
.TP
memory\-reflect(1)
Run a Hermes reflection pass now: distil recent episodes into memories
.TP
memory\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
CATEGORIES:
  fact        Infrastructure facts (OS, IPs, services)
  preference  How you like things done
  pattern     Recurring issues or solutions
  project     Project\-specific context
  skill       Learned operational procedures
  person      Team member info

EXAMPLES:
  regin memory save fact \*(AqProduction DB is PostgreSQL 16 on db01\*(Aq
  regin memory save preference \*(AqAlways use apt, never snap\*(Aq
  regin memory list
  regin memory search postgres
